Center: US National Nuclear Data Center, Brookhaven, USA
title: Interference Phenomena of Slow Neutrons

x4codes.hlp: Argonne National Laboratory, Argonne, IL, United States of America
Argonne National Laboratory, Argonne, IL, United States of America

x4freetext: Collimated beam of thermal neutrons emerging
from the thermal column is made monochromatic by
Bragg reflection on a Huorite crystal. It is further
collimated by passing through two very narrow cadmium
slits, 2 mm wide and about 3.5 meters apart. The
narrow monochromatic beam emerging from the second
slit falls on the mirror which can be rotated by
small angles. The reflected beam is detected by a BF3
proportional counter about 3.5 meters away and with a
cadmium entrance slit 2 mm wide. By moving the
counter across the beam, both direct and reflected
Compiler`s comment: Neutron energy is expressed in
angstrom. Using the Paul Scherrer institute
can deduce if lambda=1.5 A then En=36.364 meV.
BP: Updated to new date formats,lower
case. corrections according last EXFOR rules and
Dict. Changed reaction coding from (N,EL) to (N,THS).
Explained energy conversion from angstrom to meV. Added
doi, CF4 and H2 data. Subentries 22-24 were added.
